comments: He is a great professor. I currently have a internship in Information Technology. So, this class was a blessing to take. Dr. Dan\'s online lectures were incredibly helpful. The whole class is straightforward and to the point. Whenever he teaches something he ALWAYS gives an example, which truly helps. I also love having the lecture through a video.

comments: Dan Whitaker makes exceptional use of visual displays and hands on classroom activities to help students grasp concepts that get lost when reading technical material. Learning is easy and reinforced in each class and again before exams are taken. I wish all instructors were this well prepared to help their students succeed.

comments: The semester is not over but almost. I took this class online and it was super easy. If u watch his videos and make sure u take notes from the videos then when u take the quizzes every week u will do great! Professor Dan answered my e-mails quickly n seemed fair! Great way to go if ur only take this class because it\'s required of your major.

comments: Dr. Dan is a real headcase, avoid like a dose of the clap. He implies his PhD is in computer science, but it\'s really in education. He\'s in love with the sound of his voice, but the problem is that he makes no sense.You don\'t need this class; just get the book, the OS, and study for the MSCE exam and save your tuition.

comments: I was nervous to take this class without finding any reviews. However, I am very glad I took this class. I was very please with his enthusiasm in the material and his helpfulness. I found him to be entertaining, which made up for the basis of the subject (computer books put me to sleep!). I give Dr. Dan two thumbs up, and I highly recommend him!
